This large 1 bedroom apartment is situated on a quiet back street in histroic Trastevere. Due to its size it can easily accomodate up to 3 tenants. The spacious living room has a leather pull-out sofa bed with ample room for storage space. It has a fully equipped kitchen, with a 5-burner stovetop, oven, washing machine, full-size refridgerator, and plenty of counterspace to prepare and endulge in Italian cooking. The generously sized bedroom has 2 beds, but a third can be added, as well as floor to ceiling closets. Student should be sure to relax in the soaking tub, and enjoy the period blue tile in the bathroom.

Perfectly suited for student accommodation in downtown Barcelona, Born has been on the rise as one of the most fashionable districts starting with young artists setting up studios and then an influx of coffee shops, bars and shops. Within close proximity you can easily find yourself traveling to the districts of Ciutat Bella, La Ribera and Barceloneta.

Set up with three bedrooms, a bathroom, a kitchen, a living room and Internet, this apartment is fitting for students who are abroad in Barcelona.

&nbsp;

The Universidad apartment in Barcelona is an excellent housing option for students who are or are looking to study abroad. Centrally located in the heart of the city, with a metro station to connect students to a wide variety of areas and within walking distance from areas like Plaza Catalunya, Las Ramblas as well as popular nightlife bars and clubs.

With two bedrooms and one bathroom, this apartment can comfortably sleep 2 people. It also includes a ceiling ventilator, A/C and heating, elevator access, Internet, a washing machine and dryer, an iron, a hairdryer, and an open kitchen with all cooking appliances and a dishwasher.

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

This newly renovated apartment with a beautiful rooftop view is  the ideal place for living abroad in Florence. The location is great, only a few steps away from Ponte Vecchio and the Duomo, <span style="line-height: 1.5;">but is away from the mainstream tourism, which allows the students to really explore the region. The area is filled with numerous restaurants, art galleries, and clubs with lively nightlife. Terracotta flooring and wooden beamed ceilings maintain the feel of traditional décor. Large windows throughout flood the  apartment with natural light, and create a bright atmosphere. The open living space area consists of a comfortable sofa and a television. There is a dining area, a fully equipped kitchen, a  full bathroom, and laundry facilities. There are two bedrooms,  one of which has a queen size bed with an additional separate  bed on a built in mezzanine. There is always a quality team of  staff present to assist with whatever maintenance needs to be  done, checking in and out, as well as cleaning.</span>

€2,000 Deposit due upon arrival

&nbsp;

This Florence study abroad apartment is in a perfect location, located at the heart of all of the city’s famous landmarks. It is only a few steps away from Michelangelo’s David, Galleria Del’Accademia, and of course the Duomo.  It is in a lively area, surrounded by local markets and cafes. This spacious apartment can accommodate up to three people for a semester or long term rental. It has two bedrooms, both comfortable in size with high ceilings, and classically decorated. The master has a king bed, and the second has two singles. is a living room with a sofa bed and laundry facilities. The apartment is well furnished and has arched ceilings. The living area is illuminated by natural light and has a full-size sofa bed as well as laundry facilities. There is also an outdoor terrace, which is pretty and peaceful. Lastly, the kitchen is newly renovated; modern and fully equipped with everything you’ll need living in Florence.

&nbsp;

